Varro and Pliny the Elder use Maccius, and this was no doubt the form of the name employed by the Romans; but in the prologue to the Asinaria (vs. 11) the MSS. give Maccus. But Roman writers generally-Terence, Cicero, Horace, Gellius —use only the name Plautus.
